ific compartment of the leg. These muscles are innervated by a particular nerve that is a branch of the common fibular nerve.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior compartment of the leg\u003C/strong\u003E is innervated by the deep fibular nerve and contains muscles responsible for dorsiflexion of the foot, such as the tibialis anterior. The deep fibular nerve is a branch of the common fibular nerve.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELateral compartment of the leg\u003C/strong\u003E - This compartment is innervated by the superficial fibular nerve and is responsible for eversion of the foot.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESuperficial posterior compartment of the leg\u003C/strong\u003E - This compartment is innervated by the tibial nerve and is responsible for plantarflexion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeep posterior compartment of the leg\u003C/strong\u003E - This compartment is also innervated by the tibial nerve and is involved in plantarflexion and inversion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMedial compartment of the leg\u003C/strong\u003E - There is no distinct medial compartment in the leg; this option is incorrect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The deep fibular nerve innervates the muscles in the anterior compartment of the leg.","The anterior compartment of the leg is responsible for dorsiflexion of the foot.","The deep fibular nerve is a branch of the common fibular nerve."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Smith, R., \u0026 Wordsworth, P. (2016). Oxford textbook of 